The paper proposes a novel method for improving appearance-based gaze estimation, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The method involves using a deep convolutional network, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also presents experimental results on three datasets, which suggests that it may fall under multimedia (cs.MM) as well.
